commit.title: Revert "Lib: no more unique names for anonymous entries"
commit.message:
Revert "Lib: no more unique names for anonymous entries"

This reverts commit bb0509860454219ecdcf083a22d9c2b978fc879d.

Apparently it breaks elpi.  Quoting Enrico:
> I don't know why it is there. I think I can fix elpi even this commit
> has to stay, but having a sort of UUID for libojects is useful (eg to
> not replay them twice for example).

See https://github.com/coq/coq/pull/8064#issuecomment-405238086 for more
details.
